🐍 A Snake Stack: Triple-Layer ArchitectureA robust, browser-based Snake game featuring a three-layer architecture: a JavaScript/HTML5 frontend, a Python (Flask) backend for score persistence, and a Bash administration script for data management.
👥 AuthorsRamanshu Padole  Om Chavan  
🏗️ System ArchitectureThe project is divided into three distinct layers that communicate to ensure data integrity and performance:Frontend (JS): Handles the game loop, user input, and rendering via the Canvas API.Backend (Flask): A Python-based server that receives game results via a POST API and appends them to a flat file.Admin (Bash): A terminal-based utility to analyze and manage the game logs directly from history.txt.
🎮 Game FeaturesCore Gameplay & UIControls: Steer using Arrow Keys or WASD. Use P to pause, R to restart, and Q to quit mid-game.  Dynamic Difficulty: Select between Easy, Medium, and Hard speeds.  Customization: Changeable background themes and adjustable grid sizes.  Sound Effects: High-fidelity audio for movement, eating food, and game-over events.  Game ModesClassic: Standard snake rules—hitting walls or self results in game over.  Wrap Mode: The snake reappears on the opposite side of the screen when hitting a boundary.  Obstacle Mode: Static walls and blocks are added to the grid to increase difficulty.  Ghost Mode: The snake becomes "transparent," allowing it to pass through its own body.  Forever Mode: An invincible mode where the snake cannot die, designed for high-speed practice.  Food SystemApple: Standard growth (+1 length).  Pumpkin Pie: Rare treat that provides a significant boost (+3 length).  Golden Apple: Grants temporary immunity/invincibility for a fixed duration.  
🚀 Installation & Setup
1. PrerequisitesEnsure you have Python 3 installed. You will need the Flask library.Bashpip install flask
2. Starting the SystemTo start the Flask server and host the game:Bashpython3 app.py
Navigate to [http://127.0.0.1:5000](http://127.0.0.1:5000) in your web browser to play.🛠️ Administration UtilityThe admin.sh script provides a menu-driven interface to manage the history.txt log.Bashbash admin.sh
Functionalities include:Querying scores by Username.Viewing game analytics (mean score, survival time, cause of death).Log rotation (backing up the file and keeping the last 10 entries).Deleting entries by timestamp or username.📝 Data Format (history.txt)The backend records scores in a consistent, pipe-delimited format for easy Bash parsing:[Timestamp] Username | Mode | Score | Cause | Duration📄 Report CompilationA Makefile is provided in the report/ directory to compile the project documentation.Bashcd report
make
Requires pdflatex and bibtex to be installed on the system.